Finding 2: Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
Application: DVWA
Severity: High
OWASP Category: Injection
Endpoint:
/vulnerabilities/xss_s/
Description:
User input submitted through the guestbook is stored and rendered without proper output encoding. This allows attacker-controlled input to be displayed to all users.
Evidence:
Submitted input remained visible after page reload and was rendered directly in the HTML response.
Impact:
•	Persistent client-side compromise 
•	Session hijacking risk 
•	Malicious content delivery to all users 
Solution:
•	Encode output using context-aware encoding (e.g., htmlspecialchars) 
•	Validate input length and format 
•	Implement Content Security Policy (CSP) 

