Finding 3: Reflected Cross-Site Scripting
Application: DVWA
Severity: Medium
OWASP Category: Injection
Endpoint:
/vulnerabilities/xss_r/
Description:
User input is reflected in the response without proper sanitization or encoding, allowing manipulation of page content.
Impact:
•	User-targeted attacks 
•	Phishing and redirection risks 
Solution:
•	Encode output before rendering 
•	Validate input 
•	Avoid reflecting raw user input 

