Finding 4: Authentication Weakness (Brute Force)
Application: DVWA
Severity: Medium
OWASP Category: Identification and Authentication Failures
Endpoint:
/vulnerabilities/brute/
Description:
The application allows unlimited login attempts without rate limiting or account lockout. 
Impact:
•	Susceptible to brute force attacks 
•	Increased likelihood of credential compromise 
Solution:
•	Implement rate limiting 
•	Add account lockout after failed attempts 
•	Use CAPTCHA or Multi-Factor Authentication(MFA)


 Finding 5: Insecure Session Handling
Application: DVWA
Severity: Low
OWASP Category: Security Misconfiguration
Description:
Session cookies lacked proper security controls and flags, and were reused across requests.
Impact:
•	Potential session hijacking risk 
Solution:
•	Set HttpOnly, Secure, and SameSite flags 
•	Regenerate session IDs after login 
