 OWASP JUICE SHOP FINDINGS
Finding 7: API Authentication Handling (JWT)
Application: Juice Shop
Severity: Medium
OWASP Category: Identification and Authentication Failures
Endpoint:
/rest/user/login
Description:
The application uses JWT tokens for authentication. Improper validation or handling of tokens could lead to unauthorized access.
Evidence:
Authorization headers containing Bearer tokens were required for accessing protected endpoints.
Impact:
•	Token misuse could lead to account compromise 
•	Session hijacking risk 
Solution:
•	Validate tokens properly server-side 
•	Implement token expiration and rotation 
•	Avoid exposing sensitive token data 

