Conclusion
This assessment demonstrated how common web application vulnerabilities can be identified through manual testing and request manipulation. The findings highlight critical issues in input validation, output encoding, authentication, and access control.
Through testing both DVWA and Juice Shop, the assessment covered both traditional web applications and modern API-based architecture. The use of Burp Suite allowed for effective interception, analysis, and manipulation of HTTP requests.
Addressing these vulnerabilities would significantly improve the overall security posture of the applications.



